Spindle Motor Power
The spindle motor power for the VMC850L is 7.5 kW.

VMC850L
The VMC850L is a machine tool model with specific technical parameters including worktable dimensions, spindle speed, and axis movements.

Axis Rapid Traverse Speeds
The rapid traverse speeds for the X/Y/Z axes of the VMC850L are 24/24/15 m/min respectively.

COMMAND THE FUTURE
A marketing slogan associated with the VMC850L machine tool highlighting its advanced design features.

Worktable Dimensions
The worktable dimensions for the VMC850L are length 1000 units and width 500 units.

Spindle Speed
The maximum spindle speed of the VMC850L is 8000 revolutions per minute (r/min).

Spindle Distance to Worktable
The distance from the spindle face to the worktable is 86-686 units.

X/Y/Z Travel
The travel distances for the X, Y, and Z axes of the VMC850L machine tool are 800/500/600 units respectively.

Tool Magazine Type
The tool magazine type for the VMC850L is a 24-tool circular magazine.

Machine Weight
The approximate weight of the VMC850L is 6500 kg.

High-Speed Design
The design concept for high-speed operation in the VMC850L machine tool.

Renishaw
A UK-based company specializing in measurement and automation products, referenced in the quality control of the VMC850L.

Dynamic Stability
A key performance feature of the VMC850L, ensuring stability during high-speed operations.

Brown & Sharp
A company known for manufacturing precision measuring instruments, referenced in the quality control of the VMC850L.

Machine Dimensions
The overall dimensions of the VMC850L are length 2800 units, height 2450 units, and width 2800 units.
